Date: Mon, 6 Nov 2017 15:37:22 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] net: cdc_ether: fix divide by 0 on bad descriptors
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 2cb80187ba065d7decad7c6614e35e07aec8a974
Patch-mainline: v4.14
References: bsc#1067085 CVE-2017-16649

Setting dev->hard_mtu to 0 will cause a divide error in
usbnet_probe. Protect against devices with bogus CDC Ethernet
functional descriptors by ignoring a zero wMaxSegmentSize.

Signed-off-by: Bj√∏rn Mork <bjorn@mork.no>
Acked-by: Oliver Neukum <oneukum@suse.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Oliver Neukum <oneukum@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/usb/cdc_ether.c |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/usb/cdc_ether.c
+++ b/drivers/net/usb/cdc_ether.c
@@ -234,6 +234,8 @@ int usbnet_generic_cdc_bind(struct usbne
 					info->ether->bLength);
 				goto bad_desc;
 			}
+			if (!info->ether->wMaxSegmentSize)
+				goto bad_desc;
 			dev->hard_mtu = le16_to_cpu(
 						info->ether->wMaxSegmentSize);
 			/* because of Zaurus, we may be ignoring the host
